guidebook_guide.name: Anime North's 2022 Event Guide
guidebook_guide.description: Anime North is a celebration of anime, manga, music, games and all other forms of Japanese Culture! Located in Toronto, Canada, join us for the weekend of July 15-17, 2022 at the Toronto Congress Centre, Delta Hotel Airport and Sheraton Toronto Airport Hotel.
guidebook_guide.cog_details:
[{"title": "Registration", "content": "All registration is in the Toronto Congress Centre (South Building) Hall A. You must have proof of vaccination (digital, printout, receipt, etc) to pick up or register for a badge.

Hours:
Thursday (pickup only): 5:00 PM - 9:00 PM
Friday: 2:00 PM - 9:00 PM
Saturday: 9:00 AM - 6:00 PM
Sunday: 9:30 AM - 3:00 PM", "icon": "quick-info-person-add.png"}, {"title": "Help and Directions", "content": "If you require help, please consult our venue maps and find the nearest Con-AID location. Con-AID staff will be able to help you find an event, call for medical support, or direct you to a quiet room should any of those be needed. They can also answer questions regarding policies and procedures.", "icon": "quick-info-question-encircled.png"}, {"title": "Food in the Area", "content": "Please see our Area Map in the maps tab. There are local restaurants listed alongside that map.

Food trucks will also be available at the Toronto Congress Centre South Building in the parking lot, and Ginko's in the Delta runs a Cash-and-Carry table serving onigiri, odango, takoyaki, and more.", "icon": "quick-info-pin.png"}, {"title": "Exhibitors", "content": "Vendors, Industry, Comic Market, Pro Plaza, and Crafters Corner are open the following hours each day of the convention. You must wear a mask at all times while in these spaces:

Friday: 5:00 PM - 10:00 PM
Saturday: 10:00 AM - 8:00 PM
Sunday: 10:00 AM - 5:00 PM", "icon": "quick-info-shop.png"}, {"title": "Shuttle Bus Schedule", "content": "If you need help getting from venue to venue, please see about our shuttle buses which stop at the TCC, Delta, and Sheraton every half hour within their schedule.

Shuttle Bus Route: Approx. 30 minutes loop
TCC → Delta → Sheraton

Friday: 1:00PM to 2:00AM
Saturday: 9:00 AM to 2:00 AM
Sunday: 8:00 AM to 8:00 PM

The Shuttle Buses will stop at the hotel entrances and under the TCC water tower at the Hall F entrance.
Hall F entrance.", "icon": "quick-info-alarm.png"}]

guidebook_poi.name: Aaron Dismuke
guidebook_poi.description: Aaron Dismuke is an American voice actor, adaptive writer and director who works primarily with Funimation Entertainment.
guidebook_poi.label: Voice Actor

guidebook_poi.name: Kara Eberle
guidebook_poi.description: Kara is best known for her role as Weiss Schnee in the award-winning anime series, RWBY.
guidebook_poi.label: Voice Actor

guidebook_poi.name: Richard Epcar
guidebook_poi.description: Richard Epcar has voiced over 600 characters in games and animation, best known as the voice of Raiden in Mortal Kombat and Ben Dixon in Robotech.
guidebook_poi.label: Voice Actor

guidebook_poi.name: Caitlin Glass
guidebook_poi.description: Caitlin is a voice actress and ADR director, best known for the role of Winry Rockbell in the Fullmetal Alchemist franchise.
guidebook_poi.label: Voice Actor

guidebook_poi.name: Morgan Lauré
guidebook_poi.description: Morgan is an award winning voice actor with over 200 credits in anime, including Rei Todoroki in My Hero Academia.
guidebook_poi.label: Voice Actor

guidebook_poi.name: Ellyn Stern
guidebook_poi.description: Ellyn is well known for her voice work in animation, games and films with hundreds of titles.
guidebook_poi.label: Voice Actor

guidebook_poi.name: Arryn Zech
guidebook_poi.description: Arryn Zech is an American actress best known for her role as Blake Belladonna from RWBY.
guidebook_poi.label: Voice Actor

guidebook_poi.name: The 404s
guidebook_poi.description: The 404s are an improv comedy group and are thrilled to be back in front of a live audience at Anime North, performing multiple shows!
guidebook_poi.label: Improv Comedy Troupe

guidebook_poi.name: D20 LIVE
guidebook_poi.description: D20 Live is your favourite anime but re-enacted in a Tabletop RPG with a pack of madmen at the helm!
guidebook_poi.label: Professional RPG Group

guidebook_poi.name: Illuminair Entertainment
guidebook_poi.description: Contemporary circus troupe based in Toronto who specialize in high-calibre aerial, acrobatic, and object manipulation acts.
guidebook_poi.label: Circus Performers

guidebook_poi.name: Nagata Shachu
guidebook_poi.description: Featuring an arsenal of taiko, flutes, 3-stringed shamisen and more, Nagata Shachu will take you on a musical journey beyond all borders
guidebook_poi.label: Taiko Drummers

guidebook_poi.name: ACME
guidebook_poi.description: Formed in 2017, ACME’s line-up consists of former DIV members CHISA (vo.) and SHOGO (gt.), former ARTEMA drummer HAL, and bassist RIKITO.
guidebook_poi.label: Visual Kei Band

guidebook_poi.name: Niq van der Aa
guidebook_poi.description: Ottawa based Cosplayer, Costume designer and Drag Queen who has represented Canada at the Cosplay World Summit.
guidebook_poi.label: Cosplayer & Costume Designer

guidebook_poi.name: Jason Anarchy
guidebook_poi.description: Jason is the designer of the irreverent Drinking Quest series which is both an RPG and a Drinking Game but also a spoof of the world of gaming.
guidebook_poi.label: Game Designer

guidebook_poi.name: Christina and Martin Carr-Hunger
guidebook_poi.description: Christina and Martin have a combined 66 years of experience with everything from directing to prop building in the entertainment industry.
guidebook_poi.label: Industry Props & Costuming

guidebook_poi.name: Dr. Shelley TSivia Rabinovitch
guidebook_poi.description: Dr. Shelley TSivia Rabinovitch is a cultural anthropologist who has been Anime North's Master of Ceremonies for over 10 years.
guidebook_poi.label: Master of Ceremonies & Expert Panelist

guidebook_poi.name: Hilton George
guidebook_poi.description: Hilton is the creator and CEO of Blerdcon, the black nerd convention, held annually each summer in Washington DC.
guidebook_poi.label: Cosplayer & Founder of Blerdcon

guidebook_poi.name: Paul Hillier
guidebook_poi.description: Paul specializes in visual storytelling through editorial, fashion, wedding and cosplay photography / videography.
guidebook_poi.label: Professional Photographer

guidebook_poi.name: Marvin Mariano
guidebook_poi.description: Marvin has worked on high profile brands such as Transformers, GI Joe, Barbie and Star Wars. He is the creator of AN’s first mascot, Yli.
guidebook_poi.label: Artist & Illustrator

guidebook_poi.name: Neil Nadelman
guidebook_poi.description: Neil is long-time professional translator for various companies, including Sentai Filmworks, Right Stuf, and Media Blasters.
guidebook_poi.label: Translator & Expert Panelist

guidebook_poi.name: Samuri Dan & Jillian
guidebook_poi.description: Dan and Jillian teach sword and self defence classes, give informational panels, and perform stage shows.
guidebook_poi.label: Martial Arts Instructors

guidebook_poi.name: Sophie-chan
guidebook_poi.description: Sophie is a self-taught manga artist, author of the graphic novel "Ocean of Secrets" and the "Manga Workshop Characters".
guidebook_poi.label: Manga Artist

guidebook_poi.name: Dr. David Stephenson
guidebook_poi.description: David Stephenson is a space physicist who came to Canada from the U.K. in 1970 and has been a guest panelist and lecturer at conventions for over 40 years.
guidebook_poi.label: Expert Panelist

guidebook_poi.name: Katsura Sunshine
guidebook_poi.description: Katsura Sunshine is the first-ever Western Rakugo-ka in the Kamigata tradition and has toured over 5 continents performing in 5 languages.
guidebook_poi.label: Rakugo Master Storyteller

guidebook_poi.name: Shane Whalley
guidebook_poi.description: Shane has amassed 4 Million followers across his platforms, through positive vibes videos and helps others to find their passion.
guidebook_poi.label: Social Media Influencer

guidebook_poi.name: Lex Winter
guidebook_poi.description: Lex is a consummate fan who has lectured at 150 cons, liberarties, and universities on all manners of fandom and folklore.
guidebook_poi.label: Expert Panelist

guidebook_poi.name: Xiran Jay Zhao
guidebook_poi.description: Xiran Jay Zhao is the #1 New York Times bestselling author of the Iron Widow series and Zachary Ying and the Dragon Emperor.
guidebook_poi.label: Author and Youtuber

guidebook_poi.name: Hazumi 'Aileen' Okazaki
guidebook_poi.description: Hazumi ‘Aileen’ Okazki is a Japanese American Vtuber. Hazumi is a Lion Idol Princess who commonly uses her stage name ‘Aileen’ for covers and performances.
guidebook_poi.label: VTuber

guidebook_poi.name: DicequeenDi
guidebook_poi.description: DicequeenDi, or Di for short, is a professional GM, game-design awards judge, and researcher of tabletop roleplaying games.
guidebook_poi.label: Professional GM

guidebook_poi.name: Fumiko Hoshi
guidebook_poi.description: Fumiko Hoshi is a dead space gardener Vtuber whose streams focus on fighting games and FromSoftware titles!
guidebook_poi.label: VTuber

guidebook_poi.name: Hylo Ayane
guidebook_poi.description: Hylo is an anime girl dragon princess often seen playing a variety of games when she isn't falling asleep to nature documentaries.
guidebook_poi.label: Vtuber

guidebook_poi.name: Ironmouse
guidebook_poi.description: Ironmouse is known as the Demon Queen and as one of the top streamers and Vtubers on twitch. She is a member of VShojo.
guidebook_poi.label: VTuber - VShojo

guidebook_poi.name: Nemurenai Kai
guidebook_poi.description: Kai once came across the latest trend in Japanese content creation, Vtubing, and thought to himself. "Yo, I bet I could do that too."
guidebook_poi.label: VTuber

guidebook_poi.name: Project Melody
guidebook_poi.description: A futuristic AI gone lewd, Projekt Melody is an experienced entertainer for her audiences. She is a member of VShojo.
guidebook_poi.label: VTuber - VShojo

guidebook_poi.name: Moosuki
guidebook_poi.description: Moohayō! Moosuki is an independent Vtuber who streams on Twitch and occasionally sings and raps on YouTube.
guidebook_poi.label: VTuber

guidebook_poi.name: Haru Nishimura
guidebook_poi.description: Haru is most commonly known in the indie vtubing community as a moderator for one of the largest English speaking vtubing community: ENVtubers.
guidebook_poi.label: VTuber

guidebook_poi.name: Nyatasha Nyanners
guidebook_poi.description: Nyatasha Nyanners is a pink cat VTuber who is definitely not secretly an eldritch abomination plotting to take over the world.
guidebook_poi.label: VTuber - VShojo

guidebook_poi.name: OniGiri
guidebook_poi.description: A once terrifying Oni Warlord, Giri enjoys cooking and baking. Through the power of the internet, she is able to share this passion with her community.
guidebook_poi.label: Cooking VTuber

guidebook_poi.name: Maple Winters
guidebook_poi.description: Maple streams a variety of content including art requests, modded PC games, retro Nintendo games, hand-made crafts, karaoke, and more!
guidebook_poi.label: VTuber

guidebook_poi.name: Zentreya
guidebook_poi.description: Zentreya enjoys Gundam, Halo, and using unique models to entertain her and her audience. She is a member of VShojo.
guidebook_poi.label: VTuber - VShojo

guidebook_poi.name: Cherry Condos
guidebook_poi.description: This fresh face in Future Funk is quickly rising ranks within the scene for his sultry productions and tasty jams
guidebook_poi.label: Music Producer and DJ

guidebook_poi.name: Creep-P
guidebook_poi.description: The cutest nightmare you’ll ever meet, Creep-P is coming to make you scream at Otakubaloo 2022
guidebook_poi.label: Music Producer & DJ

guidebook_poi.name: D41N
guidebook_poi.description: D41N makes sample based music, heavily influenced by anime and otaku culture, incorporating glitchy and funky sounds.
guidebook_poi.label: Music Producer & DJ

guidebook_poi.name: Datarider
guidebook_poi.description: Datarider has been a staple in the Canadian anime convention community with the Kawaii Bass crew.
guidebook_poi.label: Music Producer & DJ

guidebook_poi.name: DJ Davide Ferrara
guidebook_poi.description: DJ Davide Ferrara has solidified himself as Canada's finest Makina DJ and producer.
guidebook_poi.label: Music Producer & DJ

guidebook_poi.name: Disko Warp
guidebook_poi.description: Disko Warp has been featured in many rhythm games, including Dance Dance Revolution, In The Groove, Pump It Up, StepManiaX and Osu!
guidebook_poi.label: Music Producer & DJ

guidebook_poi.name: DJ Dynamic
guidebook_poi.description: DJ Dynamic was the first DJ to play the AN outdoor stage, back when it was just a table with turntables set up in the parking lot.
guidebook_poi.label: DJ, MC, Community Organizer

guidebook_poi.name: Pan!c Pop
guidebook_poi.description: Pan!c Pop is one of the few acts successfully bringing Future Funk from the Internet to the stage, Pan!c Pop’s definitely one to look out for!
guidebook_poi.label: Music Producer & DJ

guidebook_poi.name: DJ Flyboy
guidebook_poi.description: Flyboy has been wowing crowds around the globe - across North America, the UK, Spain, and China!
guidebook_poi.label: DJ & Promoter

guidebook_poi.name: MaxieDaMan
guidebook_poi.description: MaxieDaMan is a self taught pianist and music producer with a love for video game tunes.
guidebook_poi.label: Music Producer & DJ

guidebook_poi.name: Sixtroke
guidebook_poi.description: Multi-genre Magical Boy, Sixtroke continues to gain recognition by redefining what it means to be "Sweet, Sour & Funky"
guidebook_poi.label: Music Producer & DJ

guidebook_poi.name: MC Gobstoppa
guidebook_poi.description: He's a radio host, music producer, and one of the world's best open format DJs.
guidebook_poi.label: DJ, MC, Music Producer

guidebook_poi.name: Tempest
guidebook_poi.description: Chris Tempest has an 18 year DJing career spanning 2 continents and is a local Hard Dance Legend.
guidebook_poi.label: Music Producer & DJ

guidebook_poi.name: Virus
guidebook_poi.description: Virus has been a hero in the UK Hardcore scene for 20+ years, enchanting thousands of ravers at countless events.
guidebook_poi.label: Music Producer & DJ

guidebook_poi.description: Nyatasha Nyanners, Ironmouse, Projekt Melody, and Zentreya take on all fans! Come interact with them using your mobile device for a truly unique AR experience while they talk about everything VShojo!
guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.description: It's tough getting started as a vtuber figuring out all the equipment and software you'll need. Never fear, our indie vtubers are going to lay it all out!

guidebook_poi.description: Paul Hillier walks you through how to capture subjects in costume, how to give models direction, and tips for shooting indoors and out!
guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.name: Katsura Sunshine Q&A
guidebook_poi.description: The rakugo master talks about his career, his greatest hits, and answers questions from his fans!
guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.name: Ninja Weapons of Death
guidebook_poi.description: Samurai Dan & Jillian present the non-traditional weapons of feudal Japan! Learn about the realities of the ninja arsenal and their mythology.
guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.name: Making it on Social Media
guidebook_poi.description: Join Shane Whalley as he talks about how to engage your audiences on social media, what metrics to follow, and what platforms fit your content.
guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.name: Xiran Jay Zhao Q&A
guidebook_poi.description: Author and YouTuber Xiran Jay Zhao talks about their career, their books Iron Widow and Zachary Ying, and takes on questions from the audience.
guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.name: Descending Stories, the Rakugo Anime
guidebook_poi.description: AKA Showa Genroku Rakugo Shinju, this breathtaking anime captures the heart and world of rakugo storytelling, and Katsura Sunshine is going to tell us all about it!
guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.description: Aaryn Zech, Kara Eberle, Aaron Dismuke, and Caitlin Glass talk about the ongoing smash hit 3D anime that recently saw its successful launch in Asia.

guidebook_poi.description: Join Arryn Zechs and Kara Eberle as they discuss their work within RWBY and talk with their fans.
guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.description: Our panelists, including Blerdcon founder Hilton George, discuss the experiences, challenges, and issues of Black, Indigenous, and people of colour (BIPOC) cosplayers, plus practical tips & inspiration. All are welcome!
guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.name: FullPanels- Meta Discussionl Alchemist
guidebook_poi.description: Join Caitlin Glass and Aaron Dismuke as they talk about their work as Winry and Alphonse in the hit franchise.
guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.name: ACME Q&A
guidebook_poi.description: ACME answers your questions! Come talk to the band about their work and their future projects.
guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.name: My Hero Academia
guidebook_poi.description: Join Aaron Dismuke, Caitlin Glass, and Morgan Laure as they talk about their work on My Hero Academia.
guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.name: Women in the Anime Industry
guidebook_poi.description: Join Ellyn Stern as she talks about how women have helped shaped the anime industry.
guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.name: Women of Voice Acting
guidebook_poi.description: Arryn Zech, Kara Eberle, Caitlin Glass, and Morgan Laure talk about their experiences as women in the voice acting industry and how the workplace looks today.
guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.description: Morgan Laure answers her fans and talks about her career.

guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.label: Guest Panels & Events

guidebook_poi.name: Mecha Musume
guidebook_poi.description: What do you get from combining kits and cute anime girls? A new trend with no end in sight! Let's go down this rabbit hole together and see how the kits have evolved.
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Military and Mecha

guidebook_poi.name: Mecha VS the Real World
guidebook_poi.description: A comparison of the tropes of anime against the realities of mechanized warfare and related technologies.
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Military and Mecha

guidebook_poi.name: Model Building for Competition
guidebook_poi.description: Let's look at how to showcase your skills to wow the judges for online or in-person judging, and create an epic centrepiece for your shelf!
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Military and Mecha

guidebook_poi.name: Gundam Tech
guidebook_poi.description: From Minovsky Particles to GN Drives and Heat weapons, we dive into what makes each Gundam universe and its technology so cool!
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Military and Mecha

guidebook_poi.name: Super Robot Classics
guidebook_poi.description: This panel is for you if you're a fan of Mazinger Z, Giant Robo, Diaclone, Gurren Lagann, Getter, and more. Let's get hotblooded with some classics of the Super Robot subgenre!
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Military and Mecha

guidebook_poi.name: The Real Battleship Yamato & Her Siblings
guidebook_poi.description: Is there Anime without Yamato? She was real, and this is a deep background presentation on Yamato and her siblings Musashi and Shinano.
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Military and Mecha

guidebook_poi.name: YTV & Anime and Its Influence on the Fans
guidebook_poi.description: The 90s and early 2000s saw YTV form a core part of anime fandom with shows like Gundam Wing and Sailor Moon, just as the boom began. What is its legacy today?
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Presentations

guidebook_poi.name: How to Plan a Fan Trip to Japan
guidebook_poi.description: Sights to see, goodies to buy, delicious food to devour- How to get started and where to go in Japan!
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Presentations

guidebook_poi.name: Japanese Apocalypticism
guidebook_poi.description: What is Japanese Apocalypticism? How do otaku think about the end of the world? From Japan Sinks to Eva to Haruhi, this presentation looks at the end of the world.
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Presentations

guidebook_poi.name: Lesbian Sex 101 (18+)
guidebook_poi.description: All about lesbian sex with a focus on 18+ yuri manga and anime.
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Presentations

guidebook_poi.name: VTubing 101
guidebook_poi.description: An introductory and instructive panel to get you started as a VTuber/streamer! Which platform is best, what equipment do you need, how to find an artist, or make your own model and more!
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Presentations

guidebook_poi.name: Art Fundamentals Through Anime
guidebook_poi.description: We will be dissecting the Anime style down to art fundamentals to learn important lessons when it comes to drawing and painting theory. Great for artists at any level.
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Presentations

guidebook_poi.name: Critically Engaging with Anime
guidebook_poi.description: Exploring the theoretical and practical frameworks fans of Japanese visual media can utilise while consuming their favourite properties.
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Presentations

guidebook_poi.name: Deities and Demons: Shin Megami Tensei
guidebook_poi.description: This panel explores how gods can become demons, and vice versa through Heian Era legends. Inspired by Shin Megami Tensei V's symbolism and duality.
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Presentations

guidebook_poi.name: Hentai of Horrors (18+)
guidebook_poi.description: Hentai of Horrors returns once again to showcase the best of the worst of terrible hentai, along with a VA contest.
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Presentations

guidebook_poi.name: Anime & Philosophy
guidebook_poi.description: Come and join us for a discussion about the themes, influences and interpretations of philosophy through Anime.
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Presentations

guidebook_poi.name: Combating Gatekeeping
guidebook_poi.description: We all say we want more friends who love anime, so why are we so harsh with newbies? An exploration of why gatekeeping happens, and how to avoid becoming a gatekeeper.
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Presentations

guidebook_poi.name: Sonic OCs: Do Not Steal
guidebook_poi.description: How to make your own Sonic the Hedgehog Original Character and how to get people on the internet to stop stealing your Sonic The Hedgehog Original Character: the panel.
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Presentations

guidebook_poi.name: Understanding Isekai
guidebook_poi.description: This presentation looks at the history, some alternative labels, their origins, and their future. We'll discuss how the modern genre is tied to the history of media evolution in Japan.
guidebook_poi.label: Panels- Presentations

guidebook_poi.name: Sakuramai Performance
guidebook_poi.description: Japanese Yosakoi dance group Sakuramai takes the stage with their energetic cheering performances!

guidebook_poi.name: 30 Minute Mission Kitbash
guidebook_poi.description: Come learn how to customize your first 30 Minute Missions gunpla kit. We will cover basic and advanced techniques! Kits and tools will be provided for this workshop.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Origami for Beginners (Paid)
guidebook_poi.description: Learn the basics and history of origami and fold a crane (orizuru) along with an instructor. $3 participation fee, max 30 participants.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Leatherworking (Paid)
guidebook_poi.description: Join the props-master from Fantastic Creations as he shows you how to cut and work leather as you make your own piece to take home with you. $5 participation fee, max 20 participants.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Resin Casting for Props and Costumes (Paid)
guidebook_poi.description: Learn how to work with and cast resin with the help of the props-master from Fantastic Creations in this 3 hour workshop. You will get a chance to actually cast a piece and take it home with you. $20 participation fee, max 30 participants.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Kintsugi Lecture and Maki-E Workshop (Paid)
guidebook_poi.description: Learn about kintsugi, repairing with gold! Followed by a maki-e workshop where we decorate gemstones using kintsugi. Check @kintsugica on Instagram. $35+HST participation fee, limited participation slots.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: LED and Fibre Optic SFX for Kimono and Cosplay (Paid)
guidebook_poi.description: Presented by H. Lee Wainwright, the grandfather of e-textiles will feature several special effects technologies used in costumes he created for Britney Spears, Missy Elliot, Robin Williams, Isaac Hayes, Alexander McQueen, and others. Kits free to the first 50 participants.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Loomis Head with Kent Burles (Free)
guidebook_poi.description: Learn from the famous Loomis method of drawing heads from Kent Burles, illustrator and Comic Artist!
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Comic Book Basics with Kent Burles (Free)
guidebook_poi.description: Have you ever wanted to make your own comic? Ken Burles will walk you throughthe concepts of layout and design, perspective, inking, cover design, etc.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Button Making (Paid)
guidebook_poi.description: Colour an existing design or create something completely original and then press it into your own button! Brought to you by Pretty Heroes and Anime North. $1 per button while supplies last.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Kigurumi Animegao Workshop (Paid)
guidebook_poi.description: Come learn about the art of Kigurumi cosplay. Become an anime character! Build your own anime face mask: $160 per premium kit, free kits also available.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Japanese Paper Cutting (Paid)
guidebook_poi.description: Participants will learn the basics of paper cutting by creating a unique 5" x 7" work of art by hand. Materials provided. Visit the Japanese Paper Cutting booth in the Pro Plaza to register. $15 participation fee.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Momo Tea: Intro to Japanese Tea (Paid)
guidebook_poi.description: Learn and taste the different types of Japanese tea. Reserve your slot at our booth in the Industry Area. Check @momoteatoronto on Instagram for details. $10+HST participation fee, limited participation slots.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Secret Teatime: Tea or Sake Cup Making (Paid)
guidebook_poi.description: Make your own ceramic cup by pinching and carving. Check @secretteatime on Instagram for details. $15+HST participation fee (+shipping if you can't pick up). Limited participation slots.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Secret Teatime: Mamezara Plate Making (Paid)
guidebook_poi.description: Make your own small ceramic plate by cutting + stamp patterning. Check @secretteatime on Instagram for details. $15+HST participation fee (+ shipping if you can't pick up). Limited participation spots.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Tarot Card Reading (Free)
guidebook_poi.description: Discover your fate and fortune! Come for a free tarot reading!
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Button Making (Paid)
guidebook_poi.description: Colour an existing design or create something completely original and then press it into your own button! Brought to you by Pretty Heroes and Anime North. $1 per button while supplies last.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Momo Tea: Matcha (Paid)
guidebook_poi.description: Learn from the master on how to make the perfect matcha and bring some home with you as well. Reserve your slot at our booth in the Industry Area. Check @momoteatoronto on Instagram for details. $30+HST participation fee, limited participation slots.
guidebook_poi.label: Workshops

guidebook_poi.name: Dave Merrill
guidebook_poi.description: The guy that does Anime North's Japanese Anime Hell every year, writes about classic anime at letsanime.blogspot.com.
guidebook_poi.label: Event Host & Expert Panelist

guidebook_poi.name: Sakuramai
guidebook_poi.description: Sakuramai is here to pump Anime North up with exciting Yosakoi dance performances!
guidebook_poi.label: Yosakoi Dance Group

guidebook_event.name: Opening Ceremonies
guidebook_event.description: Let's get Anime North's 25th Anniversary started with a bang!

guidebook_event.name: Fashion Show
guidebook_event.description: Our runway style kimono and j-fashion show, with special guests and community orgs!

guidebook_event.name: Anime Hell
guidebook_event.description: A wild ride filled with clips, shorts, CMs, goofs, tricks, spills, failures and curiosities, all about anime or Japan or Hell or both!

guidebook_event.name: The 404s Return to (Short) Form
guidebook_event.description: We're kicking off the con with a short-form improv show, so come watch us make fools of ourselves using your suggestions!

guidebook_event.name: AMV Contest Finals
guidebook_event.description: Come see the finalists in our annual Anime Music Video Contest!

guidebook_event.name: Saturday Night Masquerade
guidebook_event.description: Our major onstage costume showcase & competition. Come and see the amazing outfits entrants have spent all year on!

guidebook_event.name: The 404s Slacking Off (18+)
guidebook_event.description: Two years of the world going without pants must be celebrated as we slowly put them on again. We compete to be the Last Pants Standing and win the Golden Shorts.

guidebook_event.name: Pop Idol Dance Showcase
guidebook_event.description: Anime North's JPop and KPop-themed dance recital! Come see our passionate dancers perform their favourite routines!

guidebook_event.name: Cosplay Awards
guidebook_event.description: Awards for the Masquerade and other cosplay events.

guidebook_event.name: AN Idol Finals
guidebook_event.description: Singers take to the stage and perform their hearts out to see who will be crowned the Anime North Idol!

guidebook_event.name: The 404s x SpyxFamily: An Improv Championship!
guidebook_event.description: Two totally legitimate families - WHO ARE NOT IN ANY WAY SPIES - face off in an improv championship - but only one can claim victory as the top "totally normal" family!

guidebook_event.name: What IS Vtubing?
guidebook_event.description: It's been taking the internet by storm since 2016, and the pandemic saw the market absolutely skyrocket. What's being a Virtual YouTuber all about, anyway? Our indie vtubers discuss!

guidebook_event.name: Voice Acting & Creator Tips for Vtubers
guidebook_event.description: Join our indie vtubers as they break into the best ways to up your game, whether you're streaming on Twitch, YouTube, or another platform!

guidebook_event.name: OniGiri's Cooking Show
guidebook_event.description: It's an all new AR tubing experience! Giri's gonna cook everyone an awesome meal in real time with input from the audience!

guidebook_event.name: KPOP Random Dance Challenge
guidebook_event.description: What it says on the tin! Show us your best skills and dance it out to a dizzying array of KPop songs!

guidebook_event.name: VShojo Q&A
guidebook_event.description: Nyatasha Nyanners, Ironmouse, Projekt Melody, and Zentreya take on all fans! Come interact with them using your mobile device for a truly unique AR experience while they talk about everything VShojo!

guidebook_event.name: Becoming a Vtuber: The Practical Stuff
guidebook_event.description: It's tough getting started as a vtuber figuring out all the equipment and software you'll need. Never fear, our indie vtubers are going to lay it all out!

guidebook_event.name: Sakuramai Performance
guidebook_event.description: Japanese Yosakoi dance group Sakuramai takes the stage with their energetic cheering performances!

guidebook_event.name: Katsura Sunshine, Rakugo Master
guidebook_event.description: Join Katsura Sunshine as he gives a stunning rakugo performance for our Anime North audience.

guidebook_event.name: The Way of the Samurai
guidebook_event.description: Samurai Dan and Jillian present the Way of the Samurai in a live stage show, mixing combat and comedy in a dizzying trip to 16th century Japan.

guidebook_event.name: Pro Photography for Cosplay
guidebook_event.description: Paul Hillier walks you through how to capture subjects in costume, how to give models direction, and tips for shooting indoors and out!

guidebook_event.name: Katsura Sunshine Q&A
guidebook_event.description: The rakugo master talks about his career, his greatest hits, and answers questions from his fans!

guidebook_event.name: Ninja Weapons of Death
guidebook_event.description: Samurai Dan & Jillian present the non-traditional weapons of feudal Japan! Learn about the realities of the ninja arsenal and their mythology.

guidebook_event.name: Making it on Social Media
guidebook_event.description: Join Shane Whalley as he talks about how to engage your audiences on social media, what metrics to follow, and what platforms fit your content.

guidebook_event.name: Xiran Jay Zhao Q&A
guidebook_event.description: Author and YouTuber Xiran Jay Zhao talks about their career, their books Iron Widow and Zachary Ying, and takes on questions from the audience.

guidebook_event.name: Descending Stories, the Rakugo Anime
guidebook_event.description: AKA Showa Genroku Rakugo Shinju, this breathtaking anime captures the heart and world of rakugo storytelling, and Katsura Sunshine is going to tell us all about it!

guidebook_event.name: RWBY Panel
guidebook_event.description: Aaryn Zech, Kara Eberle, Aaron Dismuke, and Caitlin Glass talk about the ongoing smash hit 3D anime that recently saw its successful launch in Asia.

guidebook_event.name: YTV & Anime and Its Influence on the Fans
guidebook_event.description: The 90s and early 2000s saw YTV form a core part of anime fandom with shows like Gundam Wing and Sailor Moon, just as the boom began. What is its legacy today?

guidebook_event.name: Women of RWBY
guidebook_event.description: Join Arryn Zechs and Kara Eberle as they discuss their work within RWBY and talk with their fans.

guidebook_event.name: BIPOC Cosplay
guidebook_event.description: Our panelists, including Blerdcon founder Hilton George, discuss the experiences, challenges, and issues of Black, Indigenous, and people of colour (BIPOC) cosplayers, plus practical tips & inspiration. All are welcome!

guidebook_event.name: FullPanels- Meta Discussionl Alchemist
guidebook_event.description: Join Caitlin Glass and Aaron Dismuke as they talk about their work as Winry and Alphonse in the hit franchise.

guidebook_event.name: ACME Q&A
guidebook_event.description: ACME answers your questions! Come talk to the band about their work and their future projects.

guidebook_event.name: My Hero Academia
guidebook_event.description: Join Aaron Dismuke, Caitlin Glass, and Morgan Laure as they talk about their work on My Hero Academia.

guidebook_event.name: Women in the Anime Industry
guidebook_event.description: Join Ellyn Stern as she talks about how women have helped shaped the anime industry.

guidebook_event.name: Women of Voice Acting
guidebook_event.description: Arryn Zech, Kara Eberle, Caitlin Glass, and Morgan Laure talk about their experiences as women in the voice acting industry and how the workplace looks today.

guidebook_event.name: Lupin III
guidebook_event.description: Richard Epcar and Ellyn Stern talk about Lupin III and their history with the series.

guidebook_event.name: Samurai VS Ninja: The Quiz!
guidebook_event.description: How much do you know about the rivals of the samurai and ninja? This is the quiz! Samurai Dan is going to test you!

guidebook_event.name: IOEA Update
guidebook_event.description: The International Otaku Expo Association (IOEA) is a global association of expos and events where enthusiasts of the otaku culture may gather together. Members gather to discuss the year past and the year ahead.

guidebook_event.name: The History of Sharp Shiny Pointy Things
guidebook_event.description: Join Samurai Dan to learn about the mesmerising blades of Japan! Samurai battlefield weaponry will be displayed, explained and demonstrated.

guidebook_event.name: How to Plan a Fan Trip to Japan
guidebook_event.description: Sights to see, goodies to buy, delicious food to devour- How to get started and where to go in Japan!

guidebook_event.name: Ghost in the Shell
guidebook_event.description: Richard Epcar and Ellyn Stern talk about their work in the cyberpunk classic from Masamune Shirow and Mamoru Oshii.

guidebook_event.name: Morgan Laure Q&A
guidebook_event.description: Morgan Laure answers her fans and talks about her career.

guidebook_event.name: LGBTQ+ Book Recommendations
guidebook_event.description: Our panelists, including Xiran Jay Zhao, help you find books that represent everyone under the LGBTQ+ umbrella, from books for young readers to adult titles. There's something here for all.

guidebook_event.name: Smash Bros. Melee- Tournament
guidebook_event.description:
Will you be crowned the 2022 Melee Champion?!

Signups will open at 10:00 am on Saturday in the Ambrosia Room. There will be an entrance cap, but players who sign up after the cap is hit will be put on a waiting list to replace round 1 no-shows. guidebook_event.name: 30 Minute Mission Kitbash
guidebook_event.description: Come learn how to customize your first 30 Minute Missions gunpla kit. We will cover basic and advanced techniques! Kits and tools will be provided for this workshop.

guidebook_event.name: Animation Recommendations Beyond Japan
guidebook_event.description: Looking for shows that aren't just the current seasonal crop of anime? We've got some great recommendations from all across the world!

guidebook_event.name: Avatar The Last Airbender
guidebook_event.description: Discussing Avatar The Last Airbender, The Legend of Korra, the Kyoshi novels, comics and the future of the series.

guidebook_event.name: Avoiding Common Beginners' Sewing Mistakes
guidebook_event.description: This panel will highlight some common problems beginner sewers face and how to solve them in order to have more positive early sewing experiences.

guidebook_event.name: Berserk and Kentaro Miura (18+)
guidebook_event.description: A discussion on the legendary dark fantasy manga Berserk, its adaptations, and dearly departed creator Kentaro Miura

guidebook_event.name: BJD Trivia Snakes and Ladders
guidebook_event.description: Three audience members will be picked per session. With 3-5 sessions in a block and a winners' showdown!

guidebook_event.name: Convention Survival 101
guidebook_event.description: A panel where experienced con-goers can share tips, tricks, and knowledge to help others when attending conventions

guidebook_event.name: Cosplay for Movie Portfolios
guidebook_event.description: Cosplaying strategically to meet your career goals, with a focus on competition-level costumes, cosplay/prop making to develop a portfolio for film work, and various employment routes.

guidebook_event.name: Creepy Game Show That's Creepy
guidebook_event.description: Creepy Show is Creepy the Creeeep creep creepy game Game creepy CREEPY creep CREEPY GAME THIS IS THE CREEPY GAME CREEPY GAME NO TOUCHING NO TOUCHING N

guidebook_event.name: Critical Role
guidebook_event.description: Fellow Critters discussing Critical Role from Campaigns 1 to 3 to The Legend of Vox Machina series.

guidebook_event.name: Death Note
guidebook_event.description: Let's discuss Death Note! From the manga and anime to the Japanese movies and the incredibly butchered Netflix adaptation!

guidebook_event.name: Digimon Year in Review
guidebook_event.description: A review and commentary of and on most-things Digimon in 2021 until present; from the Digimon Adventure (2020) reboot finale, new TCG, and Ghost Game series.

guidebook_event.name: Dolly PassWord
guidebook_event.description: As you're timed, it will be your job to get your partner to guess the doll-hobby-related word through miming only. Best time between partners wins!

guidebook_event.name: Fate Series (18+)
guidebook_event.description: For all Masters and Servants who have answered the Holy Grail's call. We'll discuss the recent works from Heaven's Feel, the recent anime and of course, the Grand Order itself.

guidebook_event.name: Genshin Impact: Teyvat Travel Guide
guidebook_event.description: Let's talk about Genshin Impact's game, extras and manga lore. We'll also discuss the story and character details.

guidebook_event.name: Gundam Quote Challenge
guidebook_event.description: Let's see how good your Gundam memory is! We will be showing quotes from various Gundam series and it's up to our contestants to show us their knowledge! Prizes will be awarded to the winners!

guidebook_event.name: Honkaku: Murder Mysteries from Japan (18+)
guidebook_event.description: Honkaku Murder, the contemporary revival of the Golden Age of Mystery! Where Agatha Christie and John Dickson Carr left their pens, modern Japanese writers have taken them up again. Let's discuss!

guidebook_event.name: How to Cyperpunk Anime RPG
guidebook_event.description: How to run a really immersive cyberpunk RPG using elements of sound, visuals and storytelling.

guidebook_event.name: How to Harem: Otaku Dating Advice (18+)
guidebook_event.description: This panel will look at dating tropes/characteristics as described in Japanese anime and compare them to real-life dating data.

guidebook_event.name: Intro to Gunpla Grades
guidebook_event.description: Part building guide, part history, covering all the different types of model kits Bandai has to offer: From the simplified SD to the extravagant Perfect Grade! Come and learn what kits suit you best!

guidebook_event.name: Japanese Apocalypticism
guidebook_event.description: What is Japanese Apocalypticism? How do otaku think about the end of the world? From Japan Sinks to Eva to Haruhi, this presentation looks at the end of the world.

guidebook_event.name: Kingdom Hearts Trivia Show
guidebook_event.description: A Quiz Show for Kingdom Hearts.

guidebook_event.name: Korean Manhwa
guidebook_event.description: Chatting about Korean Manhwa overall: its tropes, its history, its relationship with Japanese media, and our favourite series.

guidebook_event.name: Lesbian Sex 101 (18+)
guidebook_event.description: All about lesbian sex with a focus on 18+ yuri manga and anime.

guidebook_event.name: Living in Japan
guidebook_event.description: Come find out some information on how you can work or study in Japan, learn general tips about travelling and Japanese culture, and share your own experiences to help others!

guidebook_event.name: Lolita Fashion Bootcamp
guidebook_event.description: We will be going over the basics of Lolita fashion with an overview of the main styles, where to buy, and etiquette within the lolita community.

guidebook_event.name: Media Preservation in a Streaming World
guidebook_event.description: We're all weebs, we have huge collections, but how can we keep them safe? Let's talk best practices, lost media, and how to keep that LaserDisc from 1983 on life support.

guidebook_event.name: Now THIS is Podcasting!
guidebook_event.description: We'll cover how to start a podcast including setup, recording, editing, guests, releases and more! Plus tips that could help YouTubers/Twitch streamers too.

guidebook_event.name: Ouji Prince Power Hour
guidebook_event.description: Are you interested in discovering your inner prince and getting started in ouji fashion? Come on down for this fun intro to a gorgeous J-fashion style!

guidebook_event.name: Ouran Host Club Gameshow
guidebook_event.description: Starting today, you are a host! Through various challenges, can we find our next honorary host club member?

guidebook_event.name: Pokemon
guidebook_event.description: A roundtable table spotlight on the Pokemon franchise, including video games, mobile games, trading card games, and merchandise

guidebook_event.name: Props & Armour - Intro To Advanced Techniques
guidebook_event.description: We'll discuss advanced construction techniques that a seasoned (or adventurous novice) cosplayer might be interested in trying out for a future project.

guidebook_event.name: Puella Magi Madoka Magica
guidebook_event.description: Covering the TV series, movies, mobile games, and fanfiction! Join us where hope and despair balance out to zero as we discuss all things Puella Magi Madoka Magica!

guidebook_event.name: Sailor Moon: The Legacy
guidebook_event.description: Discussing all things Sailor Moon: the manga, anime, live-action and musicals! We'll be including the recent Eternal movies released on Netflix.

guidebook_event.name: Shin Megami Tensei
guidebook_event.description: Join us for a roundtable discussion on Megaten's past, and the future of the franchise.

guidebook_event.name: So, You're in Love With a Fictional Character
guidebook_event.description: Talking about some of the fictional characters we've hopelessly fallen for and just how strongly they can affect us.

guidebook_event.name: Speed Art Trades: BYOS!
guidebook_event.description: Bring your sketchbook/drawing utensils! Speed dating but for art: time for speedy art trades! Bring an OC reference, and let those pencils fly.

guidebook_event.name: Strongest Trees in Anime
guidebook_event.description: Anime scenery, specifically foliage, doesn't get the attention it deserves. Come and learn how hard it would be to fell anime's toughest trees.

guidebook_event.name: The Fiction of Midway VS its Reality
guidebook_event.description: The Battle of Midway was pivotal in WWII and is represented endlessly in Anime and other popular media. This is a deep background historical presentation of what happened.

guidebook_event.name: Ultraviolent Anime (18+)
guidebook_event.description: Talking about the darker side of anime, one that saw great popularity in the 90's which is how many older fans experienced anime for the first time.

guidebook_event.name: Unpopular Opinions (18+)
guidebook_event.description: Share your unpopular opinions alongside our panelists and defend them from all scrutiny! Compete for the love (or hatred) of our audience members!

guidebook_event.name: VTubing 101
guidebook_event.description: An introductory and instructive panel to get you started as a VTuber/streamer! Which platform is best, what equipment do you need, how to find an artist, or make your own model and more!

guidebook_event.name: Wig Dyeing
guidebook_event.description: There are so many ways to dye a wig. Learn about the various ways to change a wig's colour and choose the method that works best for your upcoming project.

guidebook_event.name: Yakuza (Ryu ga Gotoku)
guidebook_event.description: With a fantastic mix of combat, story, characters, and a contained, dense, open world, Yakuza has cemented itself as a crown jewel of its genre. Come discuss this great game franchise!

guidebook_event.name: Access Japan 2000: The Untold Story
guidebook_event.description: Back in 2000, the Japanese Consulate held a festival at various points in Toronto. There was an Anime Film Festival held at the ROM during the fall. AN helped out, but that's just the beginning...

guidebook_event.name: Advanced Sewing & Construction Techniques
guidebook_event.description: Ready to take your cosplay to the next level? Join us as we discuss the sewing tips and techniques that'll help you create more polished costumes.

guidebook_event.name: An Introduction to Yokai
guidebook_event.description: Highlighting yokai in Japanese popular culture. We'll be dabbling in the origins and common traits in appearance throughout the years in Japanese media and literature.

guidebook_event.name: An Otaku's Guide to Donghua
guidebook_event.description: A look at Chinese animation (donghua) that resembles anime, plus how Chinese animation overall impacted the Japanese anime industry.

guidebook_event.name: Anime 1982
guidebook_event.description: From Space Cobras to Millennial Queens, space pirates and idol singers, 1982 put anime on the map like never before. Let's look at the films and TV series that made anime what it is!

guidebook_event.name: Anime Jeopardy
guidebook_event.description: a classic game show -- with a twist. The answers are given first, & the players give the questions. 3 contestants play in 3 rounds.

guidebook_event.name: Anisong Quiz Game
guidebook_event.description: Guess the anime song, win prizes! Compete against others to guess anime openings, endings, and even inserts. Best of luck!

guidebook_event.name: Arcane
guidebook_event.description: Arcane fans explore the fantastic worlds of Piltover and Zaun!

guidebook_event.name: Art Fundamentals Through Anime
guidebook_event.description: We will be dissecting the Anime style down to art fundamentals to learn important lessons when it comes to drawing and painting theory. Great for artists at any level.

guidebook_event.name: Attack on Titan (All Media)
guidebook_event.description: With the anime and manga concluded, come discuss everything SNK! Discussion over original theories to how the story developed over time, and fan favourite moments in the series.

guidebook_event.name: Attack on Titan (Anime Only) (18+)
guidebook_event.description: 2023 will be the finale of the series that has entranced millions since 2013. We'll review favourite scenes and talk about where the anime is at in the overall story.

guidebook_event.name: Bad Fanfiction Reading (18+)
guidebook_event.description: A live reading of truly, madly, deeply bad fanficition, unsuitable for minors, your workplace, or grammar teachers.

guidebook_event.name: BJD Swap Meet
guidebook_event.description: Have some unused BJD items collecting dust? Bring them to this Doll North swap meet! Tables will be provided to lay out your wares. Happy trading!

guidebook_event.name: Buying and Selling Gunpla
guidebook_event.description: A detailed look into the world of buying and selling Gunpla on the primary and secondary markets. Tips, tricks, and insights from the world of gunpla sale and resale, COVID edition!

guidebook_event.name: Celebrating the DiC Music of Sailor Moon
guidebook_event.description: Join Bear Sailor Moon as we celebrate the music from the DiC dub of Sailor Moon. This trip down memory lane is one that you won't want to miss! (With an interview from Michael Benghait)

guidebook_event.name: Congoing on a Budget
guidebook_event.description: Cons can be expensive to attend, but they don't have to be! Come learn new tips to attend cons for less.

guidebook_event.name: Cosplay from the Page
guidebook_event.description: One of the hardest thing to do is create three dimensional designs from an image or description in a book. Learn techniques for interpretation, choosing colours, and modifications to cater to body types!

guidebook_event.name: Critically Engaging with Anime
guidebook_event.description: Exploring the theoretical and practical frameworks fans of Japanese visual media can utilise while consuming their favourite properties.

guidebook_event.name: Cult Classic: Strangers With Candy Lite!
guidebook_event.description: It's Anime North's most over-the-top, prize riddled event - if custom-tailored for a Covid-aware environment. Candy bags, pop culture, and stunts!

guidebook_event.name: Dawn of the Monsters
guidebook_event.description: Let's discuss the development and inspirations for the game Dawn of the Monsters by 13am Games.

guidebook_event.name: Deities and Demons: Shin Megami Tensei
guidebook_event.description: This panel explores how gods can become demons, and vice versa through Heian Era legends. Inspired by Shin Megami Tensei V's symbolism and duality.

guidebook_event.name: Doll Community Feud (18+)
guidebook_event.description: We asked, and the community answered! Now it's up to you and your team to guess the popular answers to our general questions about the Doll Hobby.

guidebook_event.name: Embellishment and Detailing in Cosplay
guidebook_event.description: From applique to sequins, rhinestones to smocking, learn how to take flat designs and make them stand out. We'll also cover how to take complicated designs and make them readable for photography/competition.

guidebook_event.name: Exploring Ball-Jointed Dolls
guidebook_event.description: Sit and learn bits of history, fun facts, collected anecdotes, and the ins and outs of the When, Why, Where, Who and What of BJDs. Questions are welcomed and encouraged!

guidebook_event.name: Fans in the Professional Workplace
guidebook_event.description: A panel for professionals who are into anime and manga. Let's discuss how to handle being a fan, how some are viewed when it's revealed, and more!

guidebook_event.name: Fashion Feud Lolita Gameshow
guidebook_event.description: Do you know your blouses from your bloomers, your Moitie from Panels- Meta Discussion? Come to play or just to watch this Family Feud style lolita fashion challenge!

guidebook_event.name: Figure Collecting
guidebook_event.description: This panel will cover the history of figures, general tips on collecting, purchasing locally vs online, using mail forwarding, and finding communities & trading groups.

guidebook_event.name: Final Fantasy XIV
guidebook_event.description: Come celebrate one of the greatest triumphs in modern MMORPGs! Meet other WoLs, discuss your favourite jobs, NPCs, questlines, and expansions!

guidebook_event.name: Fruits Basket
guidebook_event.description: The new anime, the old, and the manga! How did they all compare and stack up? New ending or old ending? Join us as we discuss everything Fruits Basket!

guidebook_event.name: Furries? In My Anime?!
guidebook_event.description: Furry or Fur-Curious? We'll look at furry/furry-adjacent characters in anime, fursuiting compared to cosplaying, and furry/furry-adjacent meetups and icebreakers.

guidebook_event.name: Game Collecting
guidebook_event.description: What goes into a great video game collection, how to build up yours, and an overview of how the hobby has changed in recent years.

guidebook_event.name: Getting on the JET Programme
guidebook_event.description: Interested in teaching English in Japan? We give the lowdown on the Japan Exchange and Teaching (JET) Programme, the application process, and tips and tricks to get that interview.

guidebook_event.name: Gundam: Universal Century 101
guidebook_event.description: A retrospective of the Universal Century, what many call Gundam UC. We're exploring the main classics such as 0079, but also a few side stories, as well as a full evolution of its mobile suits.

guidebook_event.name: Han Chinese Clothing - Since the Pandemic
guidebook_event.description: Here's the story: the hanfu industry in China exploded in 2019, and tensions rise with Korea about what is hanfu/hanbok. Let's discuss!

guidebook_event.name: Hentai 101 (18+)
guidebook_event.description: A very serious discussion about the history, themes, and enduring popularity of eromanga and eroanime

guidebook_event.name: Hentai of Horrors (18+)
guidebook_event.description: Hentai of Horrors returns once again to showcase the best of the worst of terrible hentai, along with a VA contest.

guidebook_event.name: History of Anime Tabletop RPGs
guidebook_event.description: Want to learn about the best anime tabletops on the market right now? Join TTRPG analyst Di and maybe you'll learn to keikaku* your bankai into a new system. She's not sorry for that joke.

guidebook_event.name: Hosting a Lolita Meetup
guidebook_event.description: The Good, the Bad, and the Ugly of hosting a lolita meetup. We'll discuss how many people to invite, what type of activities you'll want to do, costs, and finding a venue.

guidebook_event.name: Introduction to Tarot
guidebook_event.description: This course will explain what tarot is and how it is used. We will also discuss the history, philosophy and symbolism of this divination tool.

guidebook_event.name: Japanese Culture and Anime Tourism
guidebook_event.description: A Canadian who loves Anime and has lived in Japan, along with a travel expert from the Japan National Tourism Organization (JNTO), will provide an information session on Japanese culture and Anime Tourism.

guidebook_event.name: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure
guidebook_event.description: Spanning over 30 years, this renowned series has been influential worldwide. Let's talk about it and its new Netflix anime.

guidebook_event.name: Jujutsu Kaisen
guidebook_event.description: Come and chat about one of the hottest new Shonen series airing now! Discussions about the anime, movie, speculations about season 2, and the manga so far.

guidebook_event.name: Kimono 101
guidebook_event.description: An introduction to kimono, where we explore its history, the types and formality of kimono, how a kimono coordinate is put together, motifs and seasonality.

guidebook_event.name: Lolita Pose Off
guidebook_event.description: Learn how to strut your stuff with this intro to fashion posing! Volunteers from the audience will compete in a walk-off, with the winner being crowned this year's ultimate poser!

guidebook_event.name: Mahou Shojo - Magical Girls
guidebook_event.description: Discussing Shojo and Magical Girl anime such as Pretty Cure, Mermaid Melody, Sailor Moon, Magica Madoka, Shugo Chara, Cardcaptor Sakura, Umaru, and more!

guidebook_event.name: Mecha Musume
guidebook_event.description: What do you get from combining kits and cute anime girls? A new trend with no end in sight! Let's go down this rabbit hole together and see how the kits have evolved.

guidebook_event.name: Mecha VS the Real World
guidebook_event.description: A comparison of the tropes of anime against the realities of mechanized warfare and related technologies.

guidebook_event.name: Model Building for Competition
guidebook_event.description: Let's look at how to showcase your skills to wow the judges for online or in-person judging, and create an epic centrepiece for your shelf!

guidebook_event.name: My Hero Academia
guidebook_event.description: About Deku's journey to becoming the number one hero! Do you wish they handled any arc differently? (Nothing beyond what's already been shown in the Anime.)

guidebook_event.name: Neon Genesis Evangelion
guidebook_event.description: Everything Evangelion, from development of the original television anime to an analysis of the recently released finale, 3.0+1.0.

guidebook_event.name: Pokemon Biology
guidebook_event.description: Come discuss biological theories behind your favourite Pokemon!

guidebook_event.name: Posing for Cosplay Photography
guidebook_event.description: Get better photos of yourself in costume, and feel more confident when stopped for a picture! With tips for hall photos and photoshoots. Brought to you by Elemental Photography.

guidebook_event.name: Press Your Luck
guidebook_event.description: The game of Big Bucks is back, bigger and better than ever! Join us for an exciting game full of luck and strategy, but avoid those pesky Whammies!

guidebook_event.name: Ranking of Kings
guidebook_event.description: A stellar anime that leaves room for so much discussion and interpretation! We'll discuss the first season, characters, and also the future potential of the series.

guidebook_event.name: Real Time Game Design
guidebook_event.description: Indie game designer Jason Anarchy will take a prompt from the audience and walk them through the process of designing and then self publishing this sample game idea. This panel is for viewers that are interested in game design, self publishing or both.

guidebook_event.name: Relationship Dynamics of Alternate Universes
guidebook_event.description: Discussing the sexual dynamics found in common AU themes - Alphas/Betas, slave-verses, BDSM, & more.

guidebook_event.name: Repurposing and Upgrading Your Kimono
guidebook_event.description: Repurposing and recycling vintage Kimono for people of all ages! Add lights, change patterns, and adjust your kimono with a look to a fresh take on fashion!

guidebook_event.name: Retro Video Games
guidebook_event.description: Come talk about all of the older consoles and games that are still fondly remembered. Discuss favorites and and maybe learn about some new things that passed you by.

guidebook_event.name: Sk8 the Infinity
guidebook_event.description: Let's discuss the hit skateboarding anime of 2021! Let's theorize for season 2! What do we hope will happen?

guidebook_event.name: Smarter Anime Shopping
guidebook_event.description: Save your money, already! Shop smarter and safer at shops, conventions, resale, and online (in Canada & from Japan), for all kinds of anime products. Updated for COVID-19 restrictions.

guidebook_event.name: Spy X Family
guidebook_event.description: An amazing series of the comedic adventures of an unusual family. Not covering anything beyond what's in the anime so far.

guidebook_event.name: Streaming and Streamers
guidebook_event.description: With a variety of genres and a variety of platforms, streaming is becoming more accessible every day. Come discuss streaming tips, tricks and the medium as a whole!

guidebook_event.name: Survivability of Anime Injuries (18+)
guidebook_event.description: The life of an anime protagonist is filled with hazards; at any moment they could be shot, slashed, exploded... Odds are they'd survive. Would you?

guidebook_event.name: The Angry Gods of Heian Japan
guidebook_event.description: Samurai, flirty slice of life stories, angry ghosts, gods, and yokai. This panel looks into some of the major trends in Heian folklore, and how they shaped Japan's second millennium.

guidebook_event.name: The Legend of Zelda
guidebook_event.description: It's one of Nintendo's most iconic franchises! Come discuss your favourite games, fan theories spinoff games, the upcoming sequel to Breath of the Wild, and the future of the series!

guidebook_event.name: Thermoplastics and Cosplay
guidebook_event.description: An introduction to Thermoplastics for Cosplay with a focus on Worbla. Learn when plastic is the way to go for your next build, and tips and tricks for getting the finished result you're looking for!

guidebook_event.name: Toronto Fandom Convention History
guidebook_event.description: Take a trip back in time and look at what Toronto's fan convention scene looked like in the 1960s until the present day. Demolished hotels! Vanished conventions! Extinct fandoms!

guidebook_event.name: Totally Lame Anime
guidebook_event.description: Let Neil Nadelman take you on a magical journey through the sanitary landfills and approved waste dump sites filled with decades' worth of some of the lamest animation ever produced.

guidebook_event.name: Trends in Animation
guidebook_event.description: Looking at how animation production is shaped by the trends of big hits like Into the Spider-Verse and Arcane.

guidebook_event.name: Undertale: Mettaton's Gameshow!
guidebook_event.description: WELCOME BEAUTIES, to today's gameshow! Join our cast of characters in a number of exciting challenges that are sure to making the ratings soar!

guidebook_event.name: Utena: 25 Years of Revolution
guidebook_event.description: Discussing the manga, anime, film, stage adaptations, video games and even BESM tabletop RPG. We've got it all!

guidebook_event.name: Wa Lolita, Qi Lolita, and Han Lolita
guidebook_event.description: What Wa, Qi, and Han Lolita sub styles look like, misconceptions about the styles, and information about where to find either full outfits or components to build your own coord.

guidebook_event.name: Working in the Indie Games Industry
guidebook_event.description: What's it like to turn your love for games into a job? From the average workload for various jobs within a studio, to getting a game from prototype to release, to promoting a game, our panelists from various studios will fill you in on the tea

guidebook_event.name: Yuri 101
guidebook_event.description: An overview for those both new and familiar with Yuri, the anime/manga genre of romantic relationships between girls.

guidebook_event.name: Yuri on Ice
guidebook_event.description: Discussing the fan favourite Yuri on Ice anime and manga. Also discussing the trailer for the upcoming movie about Viktor's journey to stardom.

guidebook_event.name: Anime & Philosophy
guidebook_event.description: Come and join us for a discussion about the themes, influences and interpretations of philosophy through Anime.

guidebook_event.name: Bungou Stray Dogs
guidebook_event.description: Celebrating the love of the anime, discussing its story, the literature behind its characters, the manga, and the upcoming (just announced) Season 4.

guidebook_event.name: CaramellDANSEN Like it's 2009!
guidebook_event.description: We're only doing this once! DANSEN like it's 2009! Grab your friends and lose yourself to this silly anime-con staple!

guidebook_event.name: Combating Gatekeeping
guidebook_event.description: We all say we want more friends who love anime, so why are we so harsh with newbies? An exploration of why gatekeeping happens, and how to avoid becoming a gatekeeper.

guidebook_event.name: Conrunners Panel
guidebook_event.description: A panel for conrunners to come together, discuss the scene and how their conventions work, and network with one another.

guidebook_event.name: Crossplay and Drag
guidebook_event.description: Come learn the art of gender performance! We will be talking about makeup, proportioning and tips for achieving hyper-masculine/feminine and androgynous looks no matter your gender identity.

guidebook_event.name: Dungeons & Dragons 101: Player's Guide
guidebook_event.description: This panel is to introduce people to the role of being a player in Dungeons & Dragons 5e. We will go over the rules of the game, as well as where to find resources and rulebooks, how to join or start a game of your own, and other etiquette to bring to your table.

guidebook_event.name: Dungeons & Dragons 201: DM's Guide
guidebook_event.description: Learn the ins and outs of being a dungeon master from experienced DMs! Learn what resources you need, how to run your game, and how to solve interpersonal conflict between players.

guidebook_event.name: Dungeons and Dragons for Kids
guidebook_event.description: Wanted to know how to modify the game so it's easier for everyone? D&D for kids teaches you about small changes you can make to the game as a DM to have everyone included.

guidebook_event.name: FaB with Eric and Rob
guidebook_event.description: FAB Youtubers Eric and Rob will be providing a panel on the experience of bringing their channel Spark of Genius to the community.

guidebook_event.name: Getting Started with Cosplay
guidebook_event.description: This panel addresses the key topics that'll help speed up your learning curve as you get into the world of cosplay prop and costume making.

guidebook_event.name: Gundam Tech
guidebook_event.description: From Minovsky Particles to GN Drives and Heat weapons, we dive into what makes each Gundam universe and its technology so cool!

guidebook_event.name: Gundam Trivia Game Show
guidebook_event.description: Do you know your fact from fiction when it comes to the Gundam franchise? Plucked from the audience, four teams of two will compete to see who knows more about Gundam!

guidebook_event.name: Kingdom Hearts 101
guidebook_event.description: Discussing the Kingdom Hearts series in its entirety. Let's dive into its past and future.

guidebook_event.name: Lolita Fashion Shopping Spree
guidebook_event.description: Covering Japanese brand sites, Taobao, shopping services, and swap meets. We'll teach you how to build your wardrobe without breaking the bank. Shut up and take my money!

guidebook_event.name: My Anime Academia
guidebook_event.description: Ever "made the grade" based on your impeccable knowledge and in-depth analysis of... anime? Share your experiences with like-minded students who owe that A+ to anime.

guidebook_event.name: My Dress-Up Darling
guidebook_event.description: Cosplay, fashion, the possibility of romance and... other things. Not discussing anything beyond what's shown in the Anime.

guidebook_event.name: Nintendo Switch: The Switch Effect
guidebook_event.description: The Switch has been a massive success for Nintendo after the lacklustre sales of the Wii U. This panel will discuss the present and speculate on the future of the system.

guidebook_event.name: Pro Wrestling in Japan
guidebook_event.description: Let's talk about the Japanese pro wrestling scene, favourite wrestlers, matchups, and promotions!

guidebook_event.name: Religion & Spirituality of Japan
guidebook_event.description: Discussing the religious and spiritual traditions that have come out of Japan.

guidebook_event.name: RWBY
guidebook_event.description: Talking about upcoming RWBY projects such as RWBY Volume 9, the RWBY game Arrowfell, and the new anime RWBY: Ice Queendom.

guidebook_event.name: Sailor Moon Merchandise
guidebook_event.description: A presentation of the latest and greatest Sailor Moon merchandise. Brought to you by Pretty Heroes.

guidebook_event.name: Sci-Fi Anime & Orbital Junk
guidebook_event.description: From Salvage 1 to Space Sweepers via Planete. Space junk and its representation in fiction, and why it's not such a laughing matter. With Dr. David Stephenson.

guidebook_event.name: Social Media and Cosplay
guidebook_event.description: What effects has social media had on the cosplay community? Let's discuss the good, bad, and everything in between.

guidebook_event.name: Solo Leveling
guidebook_event.description: Discussing perhaps the most popular Manwha today, with an animated adaptation already in production! Come and ARISE (No spoilers from the light novel, comic canon only)

guidebook_event.name: Sonic OCs: Do Not Steal
guidebook_event.description: How to make your own Sonic the Hedgehog Original Character and how to get people on the internet to stop stealing your Sonic The Hedgehog Original Character: the panel.

guidebook_event.name: Steampunk Fashion
guidebook_event.description: A panel covering the basics of steampunk fashion, including where to find materials and how to create that special outfit.

guidebook_event.name: Steampunk Hacks for Thrift Store Finds
guidebook_event.description: You don't need a sewing machine or a big budget to make a great Steampunk costume. Join members of the Toronto Steampunk Society to learn thrifting tips & tricks!

guidebook_event.name: Super Robot Classics
guidebook_event.description: This panel is for you if you're a fan of Mazinger Z, Giant Robo, Diaclone, Gurren Lagann, Getter, and more. Let's get hotblooded with some classics of the Super Robot subgenre!

guidebook_event.name: Super Smash Bros.
guidebook_event.description: Super Smash Bros. is one of the biggest fighting and Nintendo game franchises in this world! The past several years have seen numerous updates to Super Smash Bros. Ultimate which are worth discussing. We will also discuss the franchise's competitive landscape, as well as its future.

guidebook_event.name: The Real Battleship Yamato & Her Siblings
guidebook_event.description: Is there Anime without Yamato? She was real, and this is a deep background presentation on Yamato and her siblings Musashi and Shinano.

guidebook_event.name: Understanding Isekai
guidebook_event.description: This presentation looks at the history, some alternative labels, their origins, and their future. We'll discuss how the modern genre is tied to the history of media evolution in Japan.

guidebook_event.name: Yaoi 101
guidebook_event.description: New to yaoi? Our panel of seasoned gurus will walk you through the wonderful world of yaoi.

guidebook_event.name: Yuri 201: Recommendations
guidebook_event.description: We'll touch on what's new in both Japan and official English-translated works, and recommend quality yuri based on your interests!

guidebook_event.name: Origami for Beginners (Paid)
guidebook_event.description: Learn the basics and history of origami and fold a crane (orizuru) along with an instructor. $3 participation fee, max 30 participants.

guidebook_event.name: Leatherworking (Paid)
guidebook_event.description: Join the props-master from Fantastic Creations as he shows you how to cut and work leather as you make your own piece to take home with you. $5 participation fee, max 20 participants.

guidebook_event.name: Resin Casting for Props and Costumes (Paid)
guidebook_event.description: Learn how to work with and cast resin with the help of the props-master from Fantastic Creations in this 3 hour workshop. You will get a chance to actually cast a piece and take it home with you. $20 participation fee, max 30 participants.

guidebook_event.name: Kintsugi Lecture and Maki-E Workshop (Paid)
guidebook_event.description: Learn about kintsugi, repairing with gold! Followed by a maki-e workshop where we decorate gemstones using kintsugi. Check @kintsugica on Instagram. $35+HST participation fee, limited participation slots.

guidebook_event.name: LED and Fibre Optic SFX for Kimono and Cosplay (Paid)
guidebook_event.description: Presented by H. Lee Wainwright, the grandfather of e-textiles will feature several special effects technologies used in costumes he created for Britney Spears, Missy Elliot, Robin Williams, Isaac Hayes, Alexander McQueen, and others. Kits free to the first 50 participants.

guidebook_event.name: Loomis Head with Kent Burles (Free)
guidebook_event.description: Learn from the famous Loomis method of drawing heads from Kent Burles, illustrator and Comic Artist!

guidebook_event.name: Comic Book Basics with Kent Burles (Free)
guidebook_event.description: Have you ever wanted to make your own comic? Ken Burles will walk you throughthe concepts of layout and design, perspective, inking, cover design, etc.

guidebook_event.name: Button Making (Paid)
guidebook_event.description: Colour an existing design or create something completely original and then press it into your own button! Brought to you by Pretty Heroes and Anime North. $1 per button while supplies last.

guidebook_event.name: Kigurumi Animegao Workshop (Paid)
guidebook_event.description: Come learn about the art of Kigurumi cosplay. Become an anime character! Build your own anime face mask: $160 per premium kit, free kits also available.

guidebook_event.name: Japanese Paper Cutting (Paid)
guidebook_event.description: Participants will learn the basics of paper cutting by creating a unique 5" x 7" work of art by hand. Materials provided. Visit the Japanese Paper Cutting booth in the Pro Plaza to register. $15 participation fee.

guidebook_event.name: Momo Tea: Intro to Japanese Tea (Paid)
guidebook_event.description: Learn and taste the different types of Japanese tea. Reserve your slot at our booth in the Industry Area. Check @momoteatoronto on Instagram for details. $10+HST participation fee, limited participation slots.

guidebook_event.name: Secret Teatime: Tea or Sake Cup Making (Paid)
guidebook_event.description: Make your own ceramic cup by pinching and carving. Check @secretteatime on Instagram for details. $15+HST participation fee (+shipping if you can't pick up). Limited participation slots.

guidebook_event.name: Secret Teatime: Mamezara Plate Making (Paid)
guidebook_event.description: Make your own small ceramic plate by cutting + stamp patterning. Check @secretteatime on Instagram for details. $15+HST participation fee (+ shipping if you can't pick up). Limited participation spots.

guidebook_event.name: Tarot Card Reading (Free)
guidebook_event.description: Discover your fate and fortune! Come for a free tarot reading!

guidebook_event.name: Button Making (Paid)
guidebook_event.description: Colour an existing design or create something completely original and then press it into your own button! Brought to you by Pretty Heroes and Anime North. $1 per button while supplies last.

guidebook_event.name: Momo Tea: Matcha (Paid)
guidebook_event.description: Learn from the master on how to make the perfect matcha and bring some home with you as well. Reserve your slot at our booth in the Industry Area. Check @momoteatoronto on Instagram for details. $30+HST participation fee, limited participation slots.

guidebook_event.name: The Rising of the Shield Hero
Anime That Holds Up (Or Doesn't)
guidebook_event.description: Anime from the 90s! What's aged poorly and what's aged well? Let's talk about it!

guidebook_event.name: LARP 101
guidebook_event.description: Learn the basics of how to do Live Action Role Playing or LARPing, from safety with boffer weapons to getting into character!

guidebook_event.name: Star Quest: The Lost Wings of Honneamise Dub
guidebook_event.description: Did you know there's a lost dub of Gainax's Wings of Honneamise, produced for a Hollywood premiere in 1987? Neil Nadelman takes us through how it got produced.

guidebook_event.name: Black Nerds in Geekspace!
guidebook_event.description: Black nerdom has flourished from the very start. Join Hilton George as he explores it and some of its greatest contributors.

guidebook_event.name: Pioneer, Animeigo and Viz, Oh My! - Tribute to LaserDiscs
Pin and Patch Swap
guidebook_event.description: Got enamel pins or sew-on/iron-on patches you wanna trade? Come out to the swap!

guidebook_event.name: Mobile Suit Gundam Wing Endless Duel Tournament (Friday, beginning at 8 pm)
guidebook_event.description:
Join our tournament for a classic SNES anime fighter!
Signups will be on-site via form in the Ambrosia Room.
